1) Why Trees
If we want to store something that forms hierarchy. For example the computer file system
Trees with some ordering provide moderate access/search quicker than LL slower that A
Trees provide moderate insertion and deletion quicker than A slower than LL
Trees don't have upper limit on number of nodes

2) Main applications of trees include
manipulate hierarchical data
make information easy to search
manipulate sorted lists of data
as a workflow for composing digital images for visual effects
router algo
form of a multi stage decision making

3) Binary Tree
A tree whose elements have at most 2 children is called a binary tree
